Business Brief -- J. Baker Inc.:
   Net Soared to $2.5 Million
   In Fiscal Fourth Quarter
J. Baker attributed the increase in sales and earnings for
the latest quarter primarily to its two new apparel
divisions, Casual Male Big and Tall Stores, acquired in
February 1991, and WearGuard Stores, acquired in September
1991.
   For the year, the company had net of $8 million, or 78
cents a share, compared with $7.4 million, or 73 cents a
share, a year earlier. Sales in the latest year rose to
$493.5 million from $421.4 million.